Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1} into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pour the @water{450%ml} into a #measuring jug{} with the @vegetable stock paste{20%g}. Stir well and set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in an #ovenproof saucepan{} on medium-high heat (if you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a #normal saucepan{} and transfer to an #ovenproof dish{} later). When hot, add the onion and cook until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @tomato puree{30%g} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, then stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pour the stock into the rice and stir well to combine. Add the @baby plum tomatoes{190%g} and bring back to the boil. Pop a lid on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{60%g}.

While the risotto bakes, put the @wild rocket{40%g} in a #bowl{} and set aside.

When the risotto is ready, remove it from the oven and mix in the @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g}, Cheddar, @hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) and a knob of @?butter{}. Season to taste with @?salt{} and @?ground black pepper{} if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Drizzle the @pesto dressing{30%g} over the rocket and toss to coat. Serve the risotto in #bowls{} with the salad alongside. Enjoy!